article.headline: San Diego 92, CS Bakersfield 72
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Gyno Pomare had 17 points and 12 rebounds and Daniel Fleming added 16 points to lead San Diego to a 92-72 win over Cal State Bakersfield on Tuesday night. Fleming hit all six field goal attempts and was four-for-four from the free throw line for the Toreros (4-4). Brandon Johnson added 12 points and De'Jon Jackson and Theo White scored 11 apiece for San Diego. Dwuan Rice scored 18 points to lead Cal State Bakersfield (2-4), which failed to get closer than 17 points in the second half after trailing 50-32 in the first half. San Diego went on a 13-3 run that put them ahead 30-18 with 8:20 to play in the first half. Pomare had six points during the run and Danny Brown added a 3-pointer, one of six for the Toreros in the first half. The Road Runners, a perennial Division II power that is moving to Division I next season, has lost all four games against Division I teams this season. This is their first loss by more than eight points.
